eNCA's Genee Heyl reports. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -  The COVID-19 pandemic forced the world to find new ways of operating. Schools had to come up with methods of teaching long-distance. In many cases, families decided to go the online route. READ: COVID-19 in SA: Education sector voices concerns In 2018, John Shaw saw a gap in the education market and Teneo Education online school was born. It has no physical offices. Instead, it operates in cyberspace. READ: SA Lockdown: Nehawu welcomes tighter restrictions Pupils from all over the world are enrolled. Shaw has a dedicated support team which developed a programme for students who missed the second term. Students who participate in online schooling now love this new way of learning. Watch the video above for more details on this story.